1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:02,760
This is the main door of the church

2
00:00:02,986 --> 00:00:05,468
Please come inside to see it

3
00:00:08,160 --> 00:00:10,168
Here was the accountant

4
00:00:10,495 --> 00:00:14,132
He collected money for the poor

5
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,233
The accountant’s place

6
00:00:19,013 --> 00:00:22,061
Here there were forty seats

7
00:00:23,687 --> 00:00:27,297
Twenty seats on this side and twenty on that side

8
00:00:30,310 --> 00:00:32,200
The altar is here in front of you

9
00:00:34,284 --> 00:00:35,479
In this state as you see it

10
00:00:36,226 --> 00:00:39,054
And the changing of clothes was in that room

11
00:00:40,251 --> 00:00:41,458
Interviewer: Can we go there?

12
00:00:41,525 --> 00:00:42,525
Yes, please

13
00:00:49,835 --> 00:00:53,553
Interviewer: Explain the details of this hall, how was it?

14
00:00:53,721 --> 00:00:55,491
Tell us about every room here

15
00:00:55,586 --> 00:00:58,215
This is written in Armenian

16
00:00:59,792 --> 00:01:00,792
Take a picture of it

17
00:01:03,825 --> 00:01:06,770
This is a verse from the Bible

18
00:01:08,936 --> 00:01:09,941
Written in Armenian

19
00:01:12,858 --> 00:01:15,025
It was a model church

20
00:01:17,268 --> 00:01:20,528
At the top was the choir

21
00:01:20,791 --> 00:01:23,592
To sing church hymns

22
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:29,589
This is how it was before

23
00:01:30,496 --> 00:01:31,496
Anything you want

24
00:01:31,739 --> 00:01:34,947
Interviewer: We want to film the church servant’s room. Witness: This is it

25
00:01:36,169 --> 00:01:37,842
Interviewer: Shall we go there? Witness: Yes

26
00:01:44,131 --> 00:01:45,131
Nothing is visible

27
00:01:46,078 --> 00:01:47,867
Here they used to change clothes

28
00:01:50,423 --> 00:01:51,952
And in the other room over there, the same

29
00:01:52,370 --> 00:01:54,150
Interviewer: Let’s start from this room

30
00:01:54,263 --> 00:01:56,723
This room was for changing clothes

31
00:02:01,513 --> 00:02:03,934
You can’t see anything. It's all charred from the burning

32
00:02:04,894 --> 00:02:06,727
Interviewer: You can go out through the door and talk to us

33
00:02:06,794 --> 00:02:11,370
This room and that one were for the priest and the deacons

34
00:02:11,681 --> 00:02:12,693
They used to change here

35
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:14,760
This is the altar

36
00:02:15,933 --> 00:02:17,892
Our priest used to sit there, above

37
00:02:19,665 --> 00:02:22,697
And there were twelve pictures here

38
00:02:27,936 --> 00:02:29,697
Of the disciples of Christ

39
00:02:30,504 --> 00:02:32,354
Pictures of Christ’s disciples

40
00:02:47,255 --> 00:02:49,196
There was nothing left

41
00:02:49,956 --> 00:02:51,442
As you see in front of you

42
00:02:52,429 --> 00:02:54,121
It has become a place for pigeon nests

43
00:02:57,946 --> 00:03:04,554
Interviewer: Where were the musical rituals held?

44
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:05,750
At the top, at the top

45
00:03:06,759 --> 00:03:09,757
The hymns were up there, the religious hymns up at the top

46
00:03:10,377 --> 00:03:11,657
The choir

47
00:03:12,856 --> 00:03:14,315
At the top, there on the balcony

48
00:03:20,796 --> 00:03:23,129
They would go up there from outside, to the top

49
00:03:24,685 --> 00:03:28,424
Interviewer: The religious lessons and mourning gatherings, where were they held?

50
00:03:28,767 --> 00:03:30,955
Here, in the church

51
00:03:32,577 --> 00:03:33,723
Interviewer: In what place exactly?

52
00:03:35,630 --> 00:03:36,630
There

53
00:03:37,481 --> 00:03:40,854
They place the coffin of the deceased

54
00:03:41,908 --> 00:03:43,040
And pray over him

55
00:03:44,298 --> 00:03:46,872
On the third day, and on the fortieth day

56
00:03:48,612 --> 00:03:54,837
The family of the deceased would come to pray

57
00:04:02,548 --> 00:04:04,228
And there is the third room

58
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,371
It was used for baptism

59
00:04:11,376 --> 00:04:13,833
The basin there was for baptism

60
00:04:14,093 --> 00:04:16,435
When they wanted to baptize a child, it was done there

61
00:04:18,201 --> 00:04:19,497
Interviewer: Can you explain the baptism process?

62
00:04:19,538 --> 00:04:22,337
Yes, it was done in the room here

63
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,004
The child would be baptized

64
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:27,323
His name would be recorded by the clerks in the registers

65
00:04:29,175 --> 00:04:31,231
Interviewer: In this room? Witness: Yes
